1) Creating the Database Schema:
	CREATE DATABASE DormsNation

2)To Use DormsNation Database:
	Use DormsNation

3)Creating the Tables:
	
Users:
CREATE TABLE USERS (
ID INT PRIMARY KEY AUTO_INCREMENT,
Username VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL,
Password VARCHAR(64) NOT NULL,
Email VARCHAR(60) NOT NULL,
Age INT NOT NULL,
Gender VARCHAR(6) NOT NULL,
UNIQUE(EMAIL)
)
OTP: (One-Time-Password)
CREATE TABLE OTP (
    User_Email VARCHAR(60) NOT NULL,
    OTP_Value INT NOT NULL,
    Expiration_Timestamp TIMESTAMP NOT NULL,
    PRIMARY KEY (User_Email, OTP_Value),
    FOREIGN KEY (User_Email) REFERENCES USERS (Email)
)
Dorms
CREATE TABLE Dorms(
ID INT PRIMARY KEY AUTO_INCREMENT,
Title VARCHAR(64) NOT NULL,
Location VARCHAR(32) NOT NULL,
Distance INT NOT NULL,
Rating FLOAT NOT NULL,
Parking BOOLEAN NOT NULL,
SharedKitchen BOOLEAN NOT NULL,
Gender VARCHAR(10) NOT NULL,
Stars INT NOT NULL,
GoogleMap VARCHAR(128) NOT NULL,
MainImagePath TEXT NOT NULL,
UNIQUE(Title)
)
Altering Dorms table
ALTER TABLE dorms
ADD Visitors BOOLEAN DEFAULT true NOT NULL,
ADD QuiteHours int DEFAULT 0 NOT NULL,
ADD Pets BOOLEAN DEFAULT true NOT NULL,
ADD Description VARCHAR(2048) DEFAULT 'Dorm''s Description' NOT NULL,
ADD DailyHouseKeeping BOOLEAN DEFAULT true NOT NULL,
ADD SmokingArea BOOLEAN DEFAULT true NOT NULL,
ADD Wifi BOOLEAN DEFAULT true NOT NULL,
ADD Breakfast BOOLEAN DEFAULT true NOT NULL,
ADD AirConditioning BOOLEAN DEFAULT true NOT NULL,
ADD UnCutElectricity BOOLEAN DEFAULT true NOT NULL;

ALTER TABLE dorms 
CHANGE COLUMN Description TEXT NOT NULL ;

DormRooms:
CREATE TABLE DormRooms(
ID INT PRIMARY KEY AUTO_INCREMENT,
Dorm_ID INT NOT NULL,
Title VARCHAR(64) NOT NULL,
Capacity INT NOT NULL,
Beds VARCHAR(64) NOT NULL,
Area INT NOT NULL,
Price INT NOT NULL,
Tv BOOLEAN NOT NULL,
Wind BOOLEAN NOT NULL,
Balcony BOOLEAN NOT NULL,
ClothesIron BOOLEAN NOT NULL,
Count INT NOT NULL,
FOREIGN KEY (Dorm_ID) REFERENCES Dorms (ID),
UNIQUE(Title)
)
Bookings:
CREATE TABLE Bookings(
ID INT PRIMARY KEY AUTO_INCREMENT,
Dorm_ID INT NOT NULL,
Room_ID INT NOT NULL,
Guest_ID INT NOT NULL,
Checkin DATE NOT NULL,
Checkout DATE NOT NULL,
FOREIGN KEY (Dorm_ID) REFERENCES Dorms (ID),
FOREIGN KEY (Room_ID) REFERENCES DormRooms (ID),
FOREIGN KEY (Guest_ID) REFERENCES Users (ID),
)
ALTER TABLE Bookings
DROP FOREIGN KEY bookings_ibfk_3;
ALTER TABLE Bookings
MODIFY COLUMN ID VARCHAR(100);
ALTER TABLE Bookings
Add COLUMN Shared BOOLEAN DEFAULT FALSE;
ALTER TABLE `dormsnation`.`bookings` 
ADD COLUMN `Price` INT NOT NULL DEFAULT 1000 AFTER `Shared`;


DormImages:
CREATE TABLE dormimages(
ID INT PRIMARY KEY AUTO_INCREMENT,
Dorm_ID INT NOT NULL,
ImagePath TEXT NOT NULL,
FOREIGN KEY (Dorm_ID) REFERENCES Dorms (ID)
)
RoomImages:
CREATE TABLE roomimages(
ID INT PRIMARY KEY AUTO_INCREMENT,
Room_ID INT NOT NULL,
ImagePath TEXT NOT NULL,
FOREIGN KEY (Room_ID) REFERENCES dormrooms (ID)
)

5) Search Engine: (The simplest one, the one with filters included is found in spring 
boot getDesiredDorms method, it's the same one, but some conditions for the filters are added to it)
SELECT
    d.ID AS DormID,
    d.title AS DormTitle,
    d.location,
    d.rating,
    d.parking,
    d.SharedKitchen,
    d.gender,
    d.distance,
    d.stars,
    d.MainImagePath,
    MIN(dr.Capacity) AS RoomCapacity,
    MIN(dr.price) AS CheapestPrice
FROM
    dorms d
JOIN
    dormRooms dr ON d.ID = dr.Dorm_ID
LEFT JOIN
    bookings b ON dr.Dorm_ID = b.Dorm_ID AND dr.ID = b.Room_ID
WHERE
    d.location = ?
    AND dr.Capacity >= ?
    AND (
        NOT EXISTS (
            SELECT 1
            FROM bookings b
            WHERE b.Dorm_ID = dr.Dorm_ID AND b.Room_ID = dr.ID
                AND (b.Checkout >= ? AND b.Checkin <= ?)
        )
        OR (
            SELECT COUNT(b2.ID) 
            FROM bookings b2
            WHERE b2.Dorm_ID = dr.Dorm_ID AND b2.Room_ID = dr.ID
        ) < dr.roomcount
    )
GROUP BY
    d.ID,
    d.title,
    d.location,
    d.rating,
    d.parking,
    d.SharedKitchen,
    d.gender,
    d.distance
HAVING
    CheapestPrice IS NOT NULL
ORDER BY
    d.distance;

-------------

Fetching the fitting rooms for each form:

SELECT
    dr.ID AS RoomID,
    dr.Title AS RoomTitle,
    dr.Capacity,
    dr.Beds,
    dr.Area,
    dr.Price,
    dr.Tv,
    dr.Wind,
    dr.Balcony,
    dr.ClothesIron,
     (dr.roomcount - 
        COALESCE((
            SELECT COUNT(b2.ID)
            FROM Bookings b2
            WHERE
                b2.Dorm_ID = dr.Dorm_ID
                AND b2.Room_ID = dr.ID
                AND (
                    b2.Checkout > '2024-01-01'   
                    AND b2.Checkin < '2024-01-28' 
                )
        ), 0)
    ) AS RemainingRooms,
   dr.MainImagePath
FROM
    DormRooms dr
WHERE
    dr.Dorm_ID = 2             
    AND dr.Capacity >= 1  

    
    AND (
       
        NOT EXISTS (
            SELECT 1
            FROM Bookings b
            WHERE
                b.Dorm_ID = dr.Dorm_ID
                AND b.Room_ID = dr.ID
                AND (
                    b.Checkout > '2024-01-01' 
                    AND b.Checkin < '2024-01-28'  
                )
        )
        OR (

            COALESCE(( SELECT COUNT(b2.ID)
            FROM Bookings b2
            WHERE
                b2.Dorm_ID = dr.Dorm_ID
                AND b2.Room_ID = dr.ID
                AND (
                    b2.Checkout > '2024-01-01'  
                    AND b2.Checkin < '2024-01-28'  
                )
        ),0) < dr.roomcount
    )
    )
ORDER BY
    dr.Capacity ASC;
